nodes.bodyText:
I think we need declaration in case we want to detect a local method which contains assertions.
  @Test
  void test3() { // Noncompliant [[sc=8;ec=13]]{{Refactor this method in order to have less than 2 assertions.}}
    assertEquals(2, f(2));
    assertEquals(3, f(1));
    customAssert();
  }

  void customAssert() {
    assertEquals(2, f(2));
    assertEquals(3, f(1));
  }

In this case tree points to invocation of customAssert() while to understand whether this is an assert itself we need its declaration.

